last_replies.name: Anonymous
last_replies.com:
>Who is he?
Crona, my dearly beloved demon sword wielder.
>What series/source is he from?
Soul Eater.
>How do you feel about his series/source?
I have mixed emotions. The series overall is fun, great aesthetics and lots of value now as a nostalgic late 00s/early 10s period piece. My problem with it lies in the extent to which Crona suffers throughout much of the story, the manga continuity (the true canon) in particular. It's painful to read, and a lot of it feels rather unnecessary. Really casts a pall over the whole work.
>What are some things you love about him?
Oh man, what's not to love? He's beautiful, inside and out. His gentle demeanor, the kindness he shows his friends, his subtle and unique brand of resiliency and to that end, the way in which he's just an inherently good person. After everything he's been through, in the end he still embodies almost the polar opposite of what his mother spent many years trying to mold him into. Even claiming not to understand right and wrong, having had only a short glimpse of friendship and normal interaction in general, he kinda just does good things as though it comes to him naturally. It's so sweet.
That's not to mention his physical appeal; gorgeous STICC figure, warm and inviting and wonderfully expressive eyes, his fluffy mop of soft pink-lavender hair, so on.
>What are some of his favorite things?
He doesn't really have any, the majority of his life wasn't exactly conducive to finding things to enjoy. He did drop some apparently very intense poetry, so that could be a good lead for a pastime he might enjoy. Maybe he could even make something of a career out of it, I think a lot of people in today's bleak world could connect with his particular flavor of expression.

As an aside, it's interesting to see that almost everyone here so far has some sort of connection to or interest in the cosmos. Suppose you can add Crona to that group as well, given the outcome of the manga.
